[Name] OpenEXR 
[Summary] Tools for manipulating OpenEXR images 
[Description] OpenEXR is a high dynamic range (HDR) image file format developed
by Industrial Light & Magic for use in computer imaging applications. It 
includes support for 16-bit floating-point pixels (compatible with NVIDIA's Cg
shader language "half" datatype), several lossless compression algorithms, and
extensible image metadata attributes.)
